{"cursor":"6866","size":15,"audio":[],"currentlang":"en","article":"\n\n\n\nIn topology and related areas of mathematics, a 'neighbourhood' (or\n'neighborhood') is one of the basic concepts in a topological space. Intuitively\nspeaking, a neighbourhood of a point is a set containing the point where you can\nmove that point some amount without leaving the set.\n\nThis concept is closely related to the concepts of open set and interior.\n","linknr":262,"url":"Topological_neighbourhood","recorded":1362477257,"links":44,"instances":["topology","mathematics","topology","mathematics","mathematics","mathematics"],"pdf":[],"categories":["General topology","Mathematical analysis"],"headings":["Definition","In a metric space","Examples","Topology from neighbourhoods","Uniform neighbourhoods","Punctured neighbourhood","See also","References"],"image":["//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/8/87/Neighborhood_illust1.png/220px-Neighborhood_illust1.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/5/2/0/5206560a306a2e085a437fd258eb57ce.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/8/3/8/83878c91171338902e0fe0fb97a8c47a.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/8/3/8/83878c91171338902e0fe0fb97a8c47a.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/5/2/0/5206560a306a2e085a437fd258eb57ce.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/commons/thumb/2/21/Neighborhood_illust2.svg/220px-Neighborhood_illust2.svg.png","//bits.wikimedia.org/static-1.21wmf9/skins/common/images/magnify-clip.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/2/1/02129bb861061d1a052c592e2dc6b383.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/8/3/8/83878c91171338902e0fe0fb97a8c47a.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/2/1/02129bb861061d1a052c592e2dc6b383.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/8/3/8/83878c91171338902e0fe0fb97a8c47a.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/5/2/0/5206560a306a2e085a437fd258eb57ce.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/0/2/1/02129bb861061d1a052c592e2dc6b383.png","//upload.wikimedia.org/math/4/c/6/4c6143